1) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', cabinet size No 41128-11. Group of two. Mr Lytton in evening dress holding Mr Passmore by right arm looking at him'. 3cm x 2cm.

2) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', cabinet size No 41128-12. Group of two. Mr Lytton standing full face in evening dress with right hand out Mr Passmore standing beside him, with arms hanging down'. 3cm x 2cm.

3) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', cabinet size No 41128-13. Group of two. Mr Passmore with ermine cloak on standing looking round at Mr Lytton. Mr Lytton kicking Mr Passmore'. 3cm x 2cm.

4) 'Photograph of Miss Eva Carrington, cabinet size No 41197-1, full face in drapery, head and bust, looking up spray of large lilies each side of face'. 3cm x 2cm.

5) 'Photograph of Miss Eva Carrington, cabinet size No 41197-2, head and bust in drapery, profile spray of lilies at back of head'. 3cm x 2cm.

6) 'Photograph of Miss Eva Carrington, cabinet size No 41197-3, head and bust, ¾ face, looking round with hat on, holding muff up to face'. 3cm x 2cm.

7) 'Photograph of Miss Eva Carrington, cabinet size No 41197-4, head and bust with hat on, profile, holding up muff to side of face'. 3cm x 2cm.

8) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-7. Group of three. Miss Illington standing in centre and Miss Eva Moore standing on her right both looking at Mr Grossmith standing in check suit with left hand resting on his hip'. 3cm x 3cm.

9) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-8. Group of four sitting round dinner table. Lady and two gentlemen leaning back in chairs smoking. Miss Moore sitting looking straight in front of her'. 3cm x 3cm.

10) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-9. Group of four. Miss Moore and Mr Brown standing in centre of picture joining hands. Mr Grossmith in light suit standing with right hand raised between them. Miss Illington standing at right of picture'. 3cm x 4cm.

11) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-10. Group of six. Miss Moore, Mr Browne and Miss Illington sitting at dinner table. Mr Grossmith standing wiping cloth with serviette footman kneeling wiping carpet'. 3cm x 3cm.

12) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-11. Group of five. Miss Moore, Mr Brown, Miss Illington and Mr Grossmith sitting at dinner table, butler filling Mr Grossmith's glass'. 3cm x 3cm.

13) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-12. Group of two. Woman standing at table folding serviette. A man standing profile with left arm out'. 3cm x 4cm.

14) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-13. Group of four. Miss Eva Moore standing on stair hand on balustrade looking round, smiling. Mr Grossmith and Mr Brown standing back view looking at her. Miss Illington standing at right of picture'. 3cm x 4cm.

15) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-14. Group of three. Mr Grossmith sitting in centre in light suit. Miss Eva Moore sitting profile on his left. Miss Illington sitting on his right'. 3cm x 3cm.

16) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', cabinet size No 41153-29. Group of two. Miss Illington sitting ¾ face with hat on looking down at Mr Grossmith kneeling beside her'. 2cm x 2cm.

scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-15. Group of six. Miss Moore, Mr Brown, Miss Illington and Mr Grossmith sitting round table. One footman bending over Miss Illington, one bending over Miss Moore'.

2) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-17. Group of six. Two footmen standing by window, Miss Moore, Mr Brown, Miss Illington and Mr Grossmith seated at dinner table. Mr Grossmith's right hand up touching it with his left'.

3) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-18. Group of four seated round dinner table. Miss Moore leaning back in chair. Mr Grossmith turned slightly away from table with right hand raised'.

4) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-19. Group of five. A footman standing by window. Three seated round dinner table. Mr Grossmith standing throwing something over shoulder with right hand, others all looking at him'.

5) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-20. Group of four. Miss Moore standing full face at left of picture. Mr Browne in Scotch kilt back view. Mr Grossmith standing ¾ face in Norfolk suit and hands in pockets. Miss Illington standing at right of picture'.

6) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-22. Group of three. Mr Brown and Miss Moore standing at left with arms round each other. A postman standing at right, holding hand camera'.

7) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-24. Group of three. Miss Illington sitting holding open sunshade to hide face from postman trying to photograph her. Miss Moore standing nearly back view with hands behind back'.

8) 'Photograph of 'The Duke of Killicrankie', whole plate size No 41153-21. Group of three. Man standing holding out hat. Miss Illington and Miss Moore standing looking at him'.

9) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-1. Group of four. Mr Passmore standing holding Miss Fraser who has a cloak on. Mr Lytton holding Miss Lloyd also in cloak and hood'.

10) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-2. Group of four. Miss Fraser with cloak on sitting at left. Mr Passmore kneeling at her feet. Miss Lloyd with cloak on sitting at right. Mr Lytton kneeling'.

11) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-3. Group of four. Mr Passmore and Mr Lytton putting their heads through screen. Miss Lloyd with cloak on standing at right side. Miss Fraser standing at left'.

12) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-4. Group of four. Heads only looking through holes in screen. Miss Fraser and Miss Lloyd at the top. Mr Passmore and Mr Lytton underneath them'.

13) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-5. Group of four. Miss Lloyd and Miss Fraser behind screen putting their heads round. Mr Lytton standing shaking right fist at Mr Passmore standing at left'.

14) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-6. Group of three. Mr Passmore with ermine cloak on kissing Miss Agnes Fraser. Mr Lytton in evening dress pulling him by cloak'.

15) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-7. Group of four. Miss Fraser and Miss Lloyd standing arm in arm with gentlemen's tall hats on heads. Mr Passmore and Mr Lytton with cloaks and hoods on sitting holding open fans'.

16) 'Photograph of 'The Earl and the Girl', whole plate size No 41128-8. Group of four. Mr Lytton and Mr Passmore with cloaks and hoods on standing in centre. Miss Lloyd with gentleman's hat on standing at right. Miss Fraser with gentleman's hat on standing at left'.

scopeContent.description:
1) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-9. Group of five. Old gentleman sitting in centre holding hood over head. Clergyman standing by camera. A nurse sitting at left side of picture. A lady sitting on couch at right side and a soldier leaning over back'. 3cm x 3cm.

2) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', 12" x 10" size No 41630-2. Group. Miss Bateman in fairy's dress in centre holding wand. Four figures standing in row in front (Clown, Columbine, Harlequin and Pantaloon). Other fairies grouped at back of picture'. 4cm x 5cm.

3) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', 12" x 10" size No 41630-3. Group of four. Mr Bourchier as clown holding up open umbrella and wheeling Pantaloon in perambulator. Soldier on hands and knees on ground. A woman standing in front of perambulator'. 4cm x 5cm.

4) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', 12" x 10" size No 41630-4. Group of seven. Miss Bateman standing in centre beside Mr Robertshaw waving wand. Miss Vanbrugh as Columbine standing behind couch next to Mr Bourchier as clown. Mr Clarence as Harlequin standing at left holding Miss Grimston's hand'. 4cm x 5cm.

5) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', 12" x 10" size No 41630-5. Group of four. Mr Bourchier and Mr Valentine as clown and Pantaloon sitting on ground in centre. Miss Vanbrugh as Columbine and Mr Clarence as Harlequin standing behind them'. 4cm x 5cm.

6) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', 12" x 10" size No 41630-6. Group of Mr Valentine as Pantaloon sitting at table in centre. Mr Bourchier as clown sitting resting arm on chair. Miss Vanbrugh standing near him'. 4cm x 5cm.

7) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-7 showing two figures of Mr Valentine, one dressed as judge and one as Pantaloon looking at each other'. 4cm x 5cm.

8) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-8. Group of two. Mr Valentine as Pantaloon standing. Mr Bourchier as clown behind him, burning him with hot poker'. 4cm x 4cm.

9) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-10. Group of two. Mr Bourchier (back view) sitting playing organ. Figure of a demon coming through hole in floor'. 3cm x 4cm.

10) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-11. Group of two. Policeman holding Mr Bourchier dressed as clown'. 3cm x 4cm.

11) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-12. Group of two. Miss Jessie Bateman as a fairy holding wand sitting beside Mr Robertshaw as a demon'. 3cm x 3cm.

12) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-13. Group. Mr Jerrold Robertshaw as demon with a number of small demons each side of him, one in centre in cauldron'. 3cm x 4cm.

13) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-14. Group of two. Mr Bourchier in uniform sitting with hands on knees, looking up at Mr Robertshaw as demon standing in front of him'. 3cm x 3cm.

14) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-15. Group of three. Mr Bourchier in uniform holding paper in both hands. Miss Grimston as nurse standing beside him. A man standing on her other side'. 4cm x 3cm.

15) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-18. Group of five. Mr Valentine as judge sitting in centre. Mr Clarence touching camera. Miss Vanbrugh as a nurse at left of picture. Miss Grimstone sitting on couch looking up at Mr Bourchier in military uniform'. 3cm x 3cm.

16) 'Photograph of 'The Fairies Dilemma', whole plate size No 41630-19. Group of demons with long sticks, some pointing them at clergyman kneeling on ground at left of picture'. 3cm x 3cm.
